<h2>Esquire</h2>
<p>Wrote a <a href="esquire.html">monthly column</a> for the magazine 
for several years, until they finally noticed my taste is way too 
arty for them.</p>

<h2>Time Out New York</h2>
<p>Reviews from my tenure at <i>TONY</i> are <a href="lists.html">listed 
by year</a> on the pages for 2000&ndash;2004. Got a few other odds and ends lying around here <a href="tony.html">somewhere.</a></p>

<h2>Entertainment Weekly</h2>
<p>If anybody wants to <a 
href="http://www.ew.com/author/mike-dangelo">dig through</a> the years of 
stuff I wrote for them in the &rsquo;90s, have at it.</p>

<h2>Festival Rundowns</h2>
<p>By popular and petulant demand. Where available, links to <a 
href="festivals.html">festival 
rundowns</a> from Cannes, Toronto, NYFF, and more.</p>

<h2>Miscellany</h2>
<p>Past reviews (now with functional links! mostly to the Internet 
Archive, but still!) are available by year via the <a 
href="lists.html">Lists</a> page. There's also a page of <a 
href="vintage.html">reviews of older movies</a>.</p>

<p>Truly rabid fans can read <a href="tbc.html">a review I wrote in 
1985,</a> for <i>The 
Breakfast Club.</i> And I didn't know where else to file this <a 
href="wilkinson.html">appreciation</a> 
of Tom Wilkinson&rsquo;s performance in <i>In the Bedroom,</i> written 
for the NYFCC awards program, or my <a 
href="http://thedissolve.com/features/career-view/151-the-meticulously-constructed-film-work-of-david-ma/">exhaustive 
assessment</a> of David Mamet's entire career (as of 2013). Might as 
well throw in the pieces I've written for Oscilloscope's Musings blog, 
on <a 
href="http://musings.oscilloscope.net/post/131165054501/unfriended-and-the-shifting-definition-of-a-film"><em>Unfriended</em></a>, 
<a 
href="http://musings.oscilloscope.net/post/148750318151/too-big-a-fail-cannes-insta-flops-and-the">Cannes 
flops</a>, <a 
href="http://musings.oscilloscope.net/post/156408088566/the-counselor-no-movie-for-most-men-or"><em>The 
Counselor</em></a>, and <a 
href="http://musings.oscilloscope.net/post/168545331001/the-deepest-cut-the-hidden-emotion-of-joel-and"><em>The 
Man Who Wasn't There</em></a>. Also, a <a 
href="https://www.villagevoice.com/2018/02/15/film-poll-twin-peaks-nathan-for-you-and-the-great-tv-vs-film-debate-of-2017/">rant</a> 
about <i>Twin Peaks</i> not being a film. Oh, and a general <a 
href="https://web.archive.org/web/20141221082632/https://thedissolve.com/features/exposition/820-the-rational-wonders-of-christopher-nolan/">Dissolve 
piece</a> about Christopher Nolan.</p> 



</div><!-- This is the end of the "main" div -->


